    ResultDeserializer<java.util.Map<K,V>>

    public class ObjectMapSerializer<K,V>
extends JsonSerializer<java.util.Map<K,V>>
implements ResultDeserializer<java.util.Map<K,V>>
    Serialization for a Map using any Object key.

    The JSON format is an array with even length, alternating key and value elements. For example: [k1, v1, k2, v2, k3, v3, ...]. The keys and values may be any Object type.

    When deserialized from JSON the Map implementation is always a HashMap. When serializing to JSON any Map is permitted.
